<TEI.2><text><body><div1 type="alphabetic letter" n="B" org="uniform" sample="complete"><entryFree key="Brier" type="main" opt="n"><orth extent="full" opt="n">Brier,</orth> a prickly plant, a wild species of the rose: <cit><quote>each envious b. his weary legs doth scratch,</quote> <bibl n="shak. ven 705" default="NO" valid="yes">Ven. 705</bibl></cit>. <bibl n="shak. tmp 4.180" default="NO" valid="yes">Tp. IV, 180</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. err 2.2.180" default="NO" valid="yes">Err. II, 2, 180</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. mnd 2.1.3" default="NO" valid="yes">Mids. II, 1, 3</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. mnd 3.1.110" default="NO" valid="yes">III, 1, 110</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. mnd 3.2.29" default="NO" valid="yes">III, 2, 29</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. mnd 3.2.29" default="NO" valid="yes">III, 2, 29</bibl> <bibl n="shak. mnd 5.401.29" default="NO" valid="yes">V, 401</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. ayl 1.3.12" default="NO" valid="yes">As I, 3, 12</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. aww 4.4.32" default="NO" valid="yes">All's IV, 4, 32</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. wt 4.4.436" default="NO" valid="yes">Wint. IV, 4, 436</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. cor 3.3.51" default="NO" valid="yes">Cor. III, 3, 51</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. tit 2.3.199" default="NO" valid="yes">Tit. II, 3, 199</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. tim 4.3.422" default="NO" valid="yes">Tim. IV, 3, 422</bibl>. <cit><quote>of colour like thered rose on triumphant b.</quote> <bibl n="shak. mnd 3.1.96" default="NO" valid="yes">Mids. III, 1, 96</bibl></cit>. <cit><quote>from off this b. pluck a white rose with me,</quote> <bibl n="shak. 1h6 2.4.30" default="NO" valid="yes">H6A II, 4, 30</bibl></cit> (== rose-bush).
</entryFree></div1></body></text></TEI.2>